Package fr.univartois.cril.approximation.util.collections.dynamic

Class DynamicallyManagedIndexedCollection<E>

java.lang.Object
fr.univartois.cril.approximation.util.collections.dynamic.DynamicallyManagedIndexedCollection<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of the elements in the collection.
All Implemented Interfaces:
IndexedCollection<E>, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>
public final class DynamicallyManagedIndexedCollection<E> extends Object implements IndexedCollection<E>
The DynamicallyManagedIndexedCollection is a decorator to dynamically manage an IndexedCollection. In particular, the implementation of contains(Object) varies with the size of the collection.

      public void fastClear()
      Description copied from interface: IndexedCollection
      Fastly clears the content of this collection. After a call to this method, the collection must look empty. However, this method is not required to actually remove all the contained elements. So, use this method with caution, as it may lead to memory leaks.
